text.tspan: Play events whose time has come
Look at the score, go to the "latest" input so far
(not the more recent, but the highest scoreposition)
Is the new input note-on or note-off?
Among all the notes at this scoreposition or a bit later,
search for one that matches (and hasn't been played yet)
Look backwards, see which event already played is now being note-off'd.
Then look forward in the score to identify the note-off score event.
Did we align the input event to a score event?
NB this implies the input performance error handling:
a wrong note doesn't get matched, so is ignored.
A skipped note doesn't matter, as long as the
next note is within the search range.
Look at the newly inputted notes.
Make small adjustments to eq_time and eq_vel
to be closer to observed curve
According to the new eq_time and eq_vel,
make predictions for upcoming output events.
How should we have expected them
to be played, based on eq_time and eq_vel?
